content: We welcome some new students among us.
welcome : ) i am quite new too :p
We start with the participation check. Please everybody press I AM HERE button now, to show you are present and active. Thanks. :)
Iam too far from the server :p
Today's lesson is about d12 opening.
Surely one of the hardest ones.
How many of you have any experience about using this opening in games?
a little but I lose more time:(
You will have to give your full attention to these lessons if you want to learn d12.
Besides, I am learning together with you.
The first 4th move will be g10.
I will not spend time on 4-g9,
because that leads to i12 opening and we have been through this already.
Those who are interested may check old files.
how can i get the old file?
Use to credit point to download from www.renjuclass.com
We will not study 4-i8 because it leads to i8 opening that we h ave learned before.
And we will not study 4-i8 as it leads to d5 opening - also learned.
can you show the two 4i8 variants?
We won't study 4th moves g9, i9 and i8.
Note that when we complete all openings,
That time we will answer students questions,
and review forgotten or upgraded variants
G10 seem lost move,as I know after the game
What concerns d12 opening, we wil learn 4th moves to g10, f7, i10, g7 and g7.
Do you agree with this selection?
what's your idea about g10, ladyk?
Move 5-8 is considered the main 5th move.
So that should give easier win for black.
Let us simulate the possible continuation.
Here, passive 7-i10 is not so good.
I can only suggest this variant to the ones who want to test their skill in positional style.,
upper 8th is weaker because that white stone is wasted after next black move.
everyone give your idea for black move
it is important to be active
I am sorry. I will behave.
Can anyone explain why f7 is good?
nono, claire, you have to say it why
mooch suggested f7 first, so let him explain :P
good explanation shows you understand renju well
block other and easy link self as the same time
It blocks white's activity and creates a lot of opportunities for black
so black can conbtinue atacking without worrying about white's pattern
at the same time, stone at f7 brings the connection of f10 alive again.
and also connects to i4 point.
White is unable to do anything against such pattern?
In order to prove black's power, we do one simulation game.
I use whites and one of you will be black.
you have to win this game in few seconds
not think pof every move more than 5 seconds
it is a fancy way of proving black power.
mooch, remember, not over 5 seconds per move.
mooch you lose though, 5 second timeover
anyone else wants to prove the strength of the black power here?
Do you all agree this position is black win?
The bottom 8th is somewhat more interesting.
Indeed, regardless of the location of 8th move, black's next moves are exactly the same.
Same principle as before - defend and connect.
Does the white pair 8_10 help whites in any way?
too far away from each other
that is why black doesnt even need to block that white pair
just let it stand there alone forever
Who wants to try 5 second attack again?
this game is good place to try your skill
That is what we test here
that is how you learn about yourself
real world, never know when opponent changes the move
The VCT style should go through upper side.
So, seems like we finished this 5th move?
Other 6th moves are out of question.
How many of you know sure win here?
I do not remember all variants.
I just know the variants until  certain move...
is this a surewin position in theory?
but of course, since it is renjuclass,
i have my records beside me
unless you forget where to look :)
you are doing it now, lu
The win here... will be seen after 6 days
white has to play a four for same reason - else black goes there
OF course, black defends fromt he top.
So far the variant is logical.
The further fight goes around one main idea -
white tries to make h7 point forbidden,
whereas black tries to break it for its own advantage
We need to look several white moves here.
ok mooch, we check it first
Move 18 -h6 tries to block blacks power in bottm
compared to 19-g7, the e9 stone is more useful for black
not really a vct from left to right, but just a good connection so far
it is enough that the right side alone has enough power for vct.
Here, the usage of the e9 stone becomes clear.
The following moves , since 24th, were white's only way to gain tempo
but when they finally got it
And black just wins on the left side.
it is important that you follow the ideas now..
if you get lost now, it is hard ot understand this pattern later
So, since the point e7 gives black win...
mooch is familiar with this pattern
else white may be use g7 d7 fours
Now you all see the difference
Who wants to show black win here?
This move needs tobe explained too
else you will just wonder what is going on...
Originally, black was going to play d5 and e6,
and black should control there first
The idea of j11 is especially good because it forces white ot follow to certain point only.
so, since the right and bottom sides are so strong,
white cna only go to k11, as it needs to stop the 4x3 at g11.
So, if we look the appeared stones 27 and 28, it is a good trade in black's favor.
Upper side is safer now, besides, black has an additional pair 27_15,
So, do you all understand the usage of 27-j11 now?
Now, everything is set up nicely,
so black will go on with main idea.
There are some blocks that require good sequence of moves.
since mooch has done some work about this before,
he deserves easy life now, right?
although you know the first moves
you have to prove all possible blocks after that

if white f5 then black F7 and G7
